data.title: Nvidia to supply 260,000 AI chips to South Korean govt, Samsung, Hyundai, SK Group. Government to use 50,000 chips.
data.description: Nvidia Corporation has signed a deal to provide more than 260,000 AI chips to the South Korean government and major corporations like Samsung, Hyundai, and SK Group. The government will use over 50,000 chips for AI infrastructure, while the companies plan to deploy up to 50,000 chips in their smart factories focusing on semiconductor and vehicle production. Other partners include NAVER, Korea Institute of Science and Technology Information, and Kakao Corp. This partnership aims to drive global transformation through the production of intelligence as a new export.

data.title: VCI Global to issue 2,777,778 shares at $1.80 each in $5M direct offering; deal set to close Oct. 31, 2025.
data.description: On October 31, 2025, VCI Global Limited, a prominent business and technology consulting services provider listed on NASDAQ under the ticker symbol VCIG, revealed a definitive agreement with a single institutional investor. The deal involves the issuance and sale of 2,777,778 ordinary shares at $1.80 per share in a registered direct offering compliant with Nasdaq regulations. The transaction is anticipated to close around the same day, subject to standard closing prerequisites.

data.title: Hong Kong financial leaders visit Riyadh for collaboration, gaining insights into Saudi Arabia’s financial landscape.
data.description: Recently, the Hong Kong Academy of Finance wrapped up a visit to Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, with the aim of enhancing financial cooperation and understanding the financial landscape of Saudi Arabia. The trip provided valuable insights into Saudi Arabia’s financial ecosystem and promoted collaboration between the two entities. The visit included meetings with key industry stakeholders and institutions, fostering relationships and knowledge sharing. This initiative highlights the importance of global partnerships in the financial sector.

data.title: OKX supports Polkadot network migration to Asset Hub; DOT transfers paused temporarily. Trading unaffected. #Crypto #Polkadot
data.description: OKX has revealed its backing for Polkadot's network migration to Asset Hub, leading to the temporary halt of DOT transfers. Trading activities on the platform will continue as normal throughout this transitional period.

data.title: Bavarian Nordic secures EU contract for up to 8 million smallpox/mpox vaccine doses to enhance preparedness.
data.description: In Copenhagen, Denmark on October 31, 2025, Bavarian Nordic A/S (OMX: BAVA) revealed it had secured a collective procurement deal from the European Commission via the Health Emergency Preparedness and Response Authority (HERA). This contract allows the EU, its member nations, and other European countries 1 to acquire a maximum of 8 million doses of Bavarian Nordic A/S's MVA-BN® smallpox/mpox vaccine.
